2007-06-14 15:00  siron

	* ChangeLog (3.11), myconf (3.10, CERTI-3_2_5, BEFORE_MERGE_WIN32),
	  RTIA/RTIA.cc (3.13, CERTI-3_2_5, BEFORE_MERGE_WIN32),
	  RTIA/RTIA_federate.cc (3.35), RTIA/TimeManagement.cc (3.16,
	  BEFORE_MERGE_WIN32), RTIA/TimeManagement.hh (3.8,
	  BEFORE_MERGE_WIN32), include/RTIambServices.hh (3.3, CERTI-3_2_5,
	  BEFORE_MERGE_WIN32), libRTI/RTIambassador.cc (3.42),
	  test/Billard/Billard.cc (3.17), test/Billard/Billard.hh (3.8):
	  Development of a blocking tick: tick2.  The first version of tick
	  returns immediately with or without the delivery of one callback.
	  This can imply an active polling in the federate code. This new
	  version waits until that one callback can be delivered. We can
	  observe a performance improvement because the OS scheduler is
	  less sollicitated.

2007-05-14 14:01  rousse

	* ChangeLog (3.10), libCERTI/Message.cc (3.33),
